	</media>
<caption>“Periodic” table of MO<sub>x</sub> nanoparticles synthesized using the slow decomposition technique. </caption></figure>
      
        <para id="id1170645339484">Among the different characterization techniques used for defining these structures, transition electron microscopy (TEM) holds the lion’s share. Nevertheless, most of the modern characterization methods are more important when it comes to understanding the properties of nanoparticles. X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS), X-ray diffraction (XRD), nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR), IR spectroscopy, Raman spectroscopy, and thermogravimetric analysis (TGA) methods are systematically used for characterization.</para>
        
      </section>
