        <para id="id1170645337512">A qualitative IR-band map is presented in <link target-id="id1170645337080"/>. The absorption bands between 4000 to 1600 cm<sup>-1</sup> represent the group frequency region and are used to identify the stretching vibrations of different bonds. At lower frequencies (from 1600 to 400 cm<sup>-1</sup>) vibrations due to intermolecular bond bending occurs upon IR excitation and therefore are usually not taken into account.</para>
 

